<div class="min-h-screen flex flex-col items-center justify-center p-8 gap-12 bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-900 text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">
  <div class="flex flex-col items-center gap-12 w-full">

    <!-- Hero Section -->
    <header class="flex flex-col items-center gap-4 text-center">
      <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold">Service Level Agreement (SLA)</h1>
      <p class="text-lg sm:text-xl max-w-xl">
        This SLA defines the scope, performance expectations, security measures, and compliance standards for our services.
      </p>
    </header>

    <!-- SLA Sections -->
    <main class="grid sm:grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-1 gap-8 w-full">

      <!-- Service Scope -->
      <section class="p-6 bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg shadow hover:shadow-lg transition">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-2">1. Service Scope</h2>
        <p>This SLA covers the delivery and operation of the following services:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside">
            <li>Core system availability and access</li>
            <li>Basic user authentication, allowing users to securely log in and log out</li>
            <li>Standard reporting and system logging</li>
            <li>Scheduled maintenance and system updates</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- Performance Metrics -->
      <section class="p-6 bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg shadow hover:shadow-lg transition">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-2">2. Performance Metrics</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside">
          <li>Service Uptime: over 80% monthly availability</li>
          <li>Planned Maintenance: Not to exceed 8 hours per month with 72 hours’ prior notice</li>
          <li>System response times are monitored, with efforts made to ensure timely responses under normal operating conditions.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- Response and Resolution -->
      <section class="p-6 bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg shadow hover:shadow-lg transition">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-2">3. Response and Resolution</h2>
        <p>Incident handling is defined by the following targets:</p>
        <table class="w-full text-left border-collapse border border-gray-300 dark:border-gray-600">
          <thead>
            <tr class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-700">
              <th class="border px-4 py-2">Severity Level</th>
              <th class="border px-4 py-2">Description</th>
              <th class="border px-4 py-2">Response Time</th>
              <th class="border px-4 py-2">Resolution Time</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td class="border px-4 py-2">Critical</td>
              <td class="border px-4 py-2">Full service outage</td>
              <td class="border px-4 py-2">≤ 1 hour</td>
              <td class="border px-4 py-2">≤ 8 hours</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800">
              <td class="border px-4 py-2">High</td>
              <td class="border px-4 py-2">Major functionality impaired</td>
              <td class="border px-4 py-2">≤ 4 hours</td>
              <td class="border px-4 py-2">≤ 24 hours</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="border px-4 py-2">Medium</td>
              <td class="border px-4 py-2">Partial service degradation</td>
              <td class="border px-4 py-2">≤ 8 hours</td>
              <td class="border px-4 py-2">≤ 3 business days</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800">
              <td class="border px-4 py-2">Low</td>
              <td class="border px-4 py-2">Minor issue or general inquiry</td>
              <td class="border px-4 py-2">≤ 24 hours</td>
              <td class="border px-4 py-2">≤ 5 business days</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </section>

      <!-- Security Measures -->
      <section class="p-6 bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg shadow hover:shadow-lg transition">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-2">4. Security Measures</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside">
            <li>Encrypted data transmission (TLS)</li>
            <li>Vulnerabilities are monitored using internal tools and addressed where possible</li>
            <li>Periodic backups of critical data are performed according to internal procedures</li>
            <li>System logs are periodically reviewed for errors or unusual activity</li>
        </ul>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">4.1 User Authentication</h2>
        <p>
          Access to our services does not require login. All core functionality is available 
          without authentication. However, optional authentication is provided for users who wish 
          to create accounts. Authentication is limited to secure 
          login and logout functionality.
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside">
          <li>Login and logout are optional and not required for general service use.</li>
          <li>User credentials are stored securely using industry-standard hashing and encryption.</li>
          <li>Account creation and deletion follow documented procedures to ensure compliance.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- Compliance Standards -->
      <section class="p-6 bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg shadow hover:shadow-lg transition">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-2">5. Compliance Standards</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside">
          <li>We promise to delete ALL userdata after our exam has finished in january.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

    </main>
  </div>
</div>
